I'm running out of file descriptors and would like to know the minimum
kernel release that supports manually increasing the number of fd and
inodes.
An example from a FAQ was:
echo "4096" >/proc/sys/kernel/file-max
echo "12288" >/proc/sys/kernel/inode-max
Thanks!
